<HEADLINE>
<P>
MEMORIAL SET FOR CARNATION OFFICIAL E.S. HARTWICK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A memorial service for Elbert S. Hartwick, retired head of the legal department 
and a director and senior vice president for the Carnation Co., will be held 
Tuesday at 10:30 a.m. at All Saints Episcopal Church in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Hartwick, a former member of the Republican State Central Committee and first 
chairman of the board of the John Thomas Dye School, a private school in 
Bel-Air, was 86 when he died in Los Angeles on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Survivors include his wife, Joy, a son, Ronald, and a grandson. In lieu of 
flowers, donations may be made to the Dye School, 11414 Chalon Road, Los 
Angeles 90049. 
</P>
