<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: CITY PANEL ENDORSES VENICE BEACH CRACKDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city Transportation Commission, seeking to ensure the safety of pedestrians 
on Ocean Front Walk in Venice and elsewhere, endorsed a proposed ordinance 
Thursday designed to crack down on reckless skateboarders, roller-skaters and 
bicyclists. The panel also approved a second ordinance that would let the 
Transportation Department establish broad restrictions over such activities. 
</P>
<P>
Both ordinances must be approved by the City Council. Councilwoman Ruth 
Galanter, who represents the Venice area, last year suggested the ban on the 
"reckless operation of human-powered wheeled vehicles" in a compromise aimed at 
finding a way for skaters and pedestrians to coexist on the popular beachfront 
without endangering each other. 
</P>
<P>
Her proposal was prompted by the repeal by the council of a 10-year-old 
ordinance banning skateboarding and roller-skating along Ocean Front Walk, 
which has been largely ignored. 
</P>
</TEXT>
