Symphony, is one of five finalists for the prestigious Seaver Conducting Award 
given every two years to young conductors. The winner, to be announced 
Saturday, will receive $150,000. St. Clair, 37, was an assistant conductor of 
the Boston Symphony when named music director in February. He starts here in 
October. Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
