<P>
A convicted burglar can be ordered to pay for a burglar alarm for his victims 
as part of restitution, the Wisconsin Supreme Court ruled. The victimized 
couple had told the trial court that the Nov. 13, 1987, burglary was traumatic, 
forcing the woman to seek medical care and prompting them to install the alarm 
system to ease their fears. 
