SAUDI KING WANTS TO HEAL RIFT WITH IRAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NICOSIA, Cyprus 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saudi Arabia's King Fahd was quoted Thursday as saying he wants to end disputes 
between his conservative kingdom and Iran. 
</P>
<P>
"With Iran in particular, we have not rejected the principle of improving the 
atmosphere with them, but we even (want) to eliminate all causes for the 
current dispute," he told the Saudi newspaper Okaz in an interview. 
</P>
<P>
Relations reached a new low after Iran said it would boycott July's Muslim 
pilgrimage to Mecca for the third year because of quota restrictions imposed by 
Saudi Arabia. 
