<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
$26,250 IN GRANTS TO BENEFIT ARTS GROUPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTOPHER REYNOLDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ventura County Community Foundation announced that it will distribute 
$26,250 in grants to 16 local arts organizations this year, an increase of 
nearly $5,000 over last year's donations to the arts. 
</P>
<P>
The 3-year-old foundation created the County Arts Alliance in 1988 as a 
cultural arm to distribute grants that previously had been doled out by the 
Ventura County Arts Commission. 
</P>
<P>
This year, $11,000 of the foundation's grants came from The James Irvine 
Foundation, a statewide charitable organization that earmarks its funds for 
rural arts programs. 
</P>
<P>
Community Foundation President Cathy Edge said most of the remaining $15,250 
came from the California Arts Council, with some additional funds generated by 
local fund raising. 
</P>
<P>
The grant recipients include: 
</P>
<P>
Santa Paula Theatre Center, $2,500; Ventura County Symphony Assn., $2,500; 
Conejo Valley Art Museum, $2,000; Buena Ventura Art Assn., $2,000; Plexus Dance 
Theatre, $1,500; Ventura Arts Council, $1,250; Conejo Symphony Orchestra, 
$1,250; Santa Susana Repertory Company, $1,250; Fine Arts for Youth, $500; and 
Xanadu Theatre, $500. 
</P>
<P>
The institutions that will share in the rural arts money include: 
</P>
<P>
Teatro Inlakech, $3,000; Illusions Theatre; $2,500; Ventura County 
Multi-Cultural Art Council, $2,500; Royal Shakespeare Revels, $2,000; Brass 
Pathetique, $500; and Preserve Bottle Village, $500. CHRISTOPHER REYNOLDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
