<HEADLINE>
<P>
MIDFIELDER SIGNS CONTRACT WITH HEAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jim Gabarra, who played for the champion San Diego Soccers of the Major Indoor 
Soccer League, has signed with the Los Angeles Heat of the American 
Professional Soccer League West. 
</P>
<P>
Gabarra is expected to start at midfield tonight when the Heat plays at the 
Seattle Storm. 
</P>
<P>
Gabarra, 30, replaces Steve Sharp, who asked for his release but instead was 
placed on the inactive reserve list. Sharp scored two goals and one assist in 
limited action. 
</P>
<P>
A native of Connecticut, Gabarra played for the Heat last season, scoring four 
goals and making three assists. Previously, he played for the United States 
National and Olympic teams. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm looking forward to being back with my old teammates and I hope I can help 
the team," Gabarra said. 
