<P>
Wild Art 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061590-0121 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 234081 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
June 15, 1990, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Orange County Life; Part N; Page 4; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
71 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOT, HIP &amp; HAPPENING: HIGH LIFE: A WEEKLY FORUM FOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TONY MARCANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Christina Hong, a senior at Mission Viejo High School, has a secret -- not only 
is she the smartest student at her school, she's also the top graduate in 
Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
Try not to spread it around. 
</P>
<P>
"I don't like to be known as the smartest person in school," said Hong, 18, who 
amassed a county-high 4.94 grade-point average and will enroll at Stanford 
University this fall. "I don't like that label." TONY MARCANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
