fit after a checkup at the nurse's station. Marcos returned after the lunch 
break looking well. However, Judge John Keenan announced that he had a cold and 
a fever and would recess the trial for the day. It is scheduled to resume 
Tuesday. Marcos allegedly plotted with her husband, former Philippines 
President Ferdinand Marcos, to divert stolen money into real estate investments 
around the world. 
