<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
ROOSEN WINS LEG OF SWISS TOUR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BASEL, Switzerland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Luc Roosen of Belgium won the third stage of the Tour of Switzerland cycling 
race today, edging a big group in a mass sprint at the finish. 
</P>
<P>
Stephan Joho of Switzerland lost time and barely managed to keep the overall 
leader's jersey. Ireland's Sean Kelly cut his lead to two seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Roosen covered the 168-kilometer leg from Aarau to Basel, including several 
steep climbs, in four hours, 18 minutes and 47 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Andrew Hampsten, a two-time winner, took 12th place, and fellow American Greg 
LeMond, warming up for a try at winning his third Tour de France, was 19th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
