<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
BAYAKOA HEADS MILADY FIELD OF 4 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A field of four headed by Bayakoa, the Eclipse Award winner as the outstanding 
older filly or mare in the country last year, has been entered in Saturday's 
$150,000-added Milady Handicap at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
Bayakoa will be ridden by Laffit Pincay and was assigned high weight of 127 
pounds for the 39th running of the 1 1/16 mile race for fillies and mares, 
3-year-olds and up. 
</P>
<P>
Others entered were Fantastic Look, who will be ridden by Kent Desormeaux and 
was assigned 113 pounds; Felidia, Martin Pedroza, 112 pounds, and Kelly, Corey 
Nakatani, 110 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
If all four entries go to the post, the total purse will be $157,200 and the 
winner will earn $89,700. 
</P>
<P>
Bayakoa, a 6-year-old daughter of Consultant's Bid, will be trying to win the 
Milady Handicap for the second straight year. If she does, she'll surpass the 
$2-million mark in career earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
