<P>
SWEDISH TEAM'S WIVES ON WAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GENOA, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The wives and girlfriends of Sweden's World Cup soccer players are flying in 
today for a weeklong visit aimed at fighting the so-called loneliness factor. 
</P>
<P>
But the wives will not be staying in the plush seaside hotel in the resort of 
Camogli where their men are based during the World Cup. 
</P>
<P>
"I really don't know when we are going to see them. I guess we'll have to sneak 
over to their place one night," striker Stefan Pettersson said with a smile. 
</P>
